main event: Two unidentified objects were sighted in the sky over Coden, Alabama on June 20, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting was both visual and radar-confirmed, lasting for 1.5 minutes.
The objects were described as moving in a southerly direction.
No photographs were taken of the objects.
The official conclusion was that the sighting was 'probably that of two aircraft maneuvering in the area'.
The witness described the objects as having a strange, vehicle-like shape that was unlike normal aircraft.
